body: "## Charter\nLiving capability epic for the CLI command surface and agent ergonomics: lifecycle primitives (create/update/close/claim/next), bulk operations, query filters, hierarchy views, output projections, and never-block error UX. pm is agent-first: every command must be usable by an agent with zero out-of-band context, and every error must carry a machine-actionable recovery path.\n\n## Scope\n- In: command surface additions/refinements, flag ergonomics, output formats (toon/json/csv/table), never-block guidance, did-you-mean suggestions, agent token-efficiency of outputs.\n- Out: MCP tool surface (pm-5k4v), storage/history internals (pm-o2kc), extension-owned commands (pm-ugqx).\n\n## Status\n97 closed children delivered the v0.1 surface (next, focus, plan family, update-many, list projections, close structured fields, shortcuts, aliases). This epic stays OPEN as a living backlog per the capability-epic convention — new command-surface work lands here.\n\n## Open children (2026-07-04)\n- pm-qt5d — --pm-path package install leaks extensions into caller workspace (path-scoping safety).\n- pm-gdi7 — unknown-option flag suggestions, list-closed projection, schema add-field help discoverability.\n- pm-b3e9 — pre-install package-owned command names should hint the owning install command."
